{
  "text": "Conversely, we infer that at KS little cycling between phases is occurring. There is no significant relationship between Fe and P, and SRP and PP. This is likely to be due to the lower concentrations of highly reactive suspended sediments for weathering, and the comparatively short water residence times of small versus large glacier systems [CITATION_1] . We postulate that water residence times (in comparison with LG) are the critical control. This is consistent with observations of Fe-P relationships at other small glaciers [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , attributed to the relatively short residence times of waters exiting the glaciers and limited secondary Fe mineral formation.",
